<zk>
	<label multiline="true">
		Test for ZK-5776: ETag and If-None-Match headers not processed correctly.

		Steps to reproduce (before fix):
		1. Set org.zkoss.web.classWebResource.cache.etag=true in zk.xml.
		2. Load the application in a browser.
		3. Open developer tools, go to the Network tab.
		4. Reload the page and observe request/response headers for a raw static resource
		   served by ClassWebResource (e.g. /js/zk/ext/fetch.js). Note: .wpd/.wcs/.dsp are
		   served by their Extendlets and were already revalidated via JspFns before this fix.
		5. On the first load an ETag response header is present, but subsequent requests
		   do NOT send If-None-Match, so the server never returns 304.

		To verify the fix:
		- Expected: after the first request, subsequent requests for the same static resource
		  include If-None-Match matching the ETag value, and the server responds with 304 Not Modified.
		- The automated test verifies the ETag response header is present when the property is enabled.
	</label>

	<button id="btn" label="Load static resource via AJAX" onClick="Clients.evalJavaScript(
		&quot;fetch(zk.ajaxResourceURI('/js/zk/ext/fetch.js')).then(r => zk.afterMount(function(){jq('#result').text(r.headers.get('ETag') || 'no-etag')}))&quot;
	)"/>
	<label id="result" value="(click button to test)"/>
</zk>
